  "why": "The paper mutates inputs at the audio-signal level using higher-level metamorphic transformations (volume, speed, pitch, filters, noise) and explicitly states that parameters are chosen conservatively so mutants remain human-recognizable. Such transformations are generally less sensitive to small floating-point precision loss from serialization. However, the paper does not explicitly state that mutations enforce input-serialization constraints (e.g., clipping/rounding to PCM integer ranges or explicit amplitude clipping to [-1,1]) nor that it generates inputs directly in a serialized format to guarantee preservation of fault-inducing perturbations. Therefore the approach fits the metric’s \"Medium\" class: using transformations less sensitive to serialization without explicit enforcement of format constraints.",
